Health & Safety Advisor
03 May 2014 06:44 AM - UAE
.
The Health & Safety Advisor role is accountable to assist the Health & Safety Manager in the leadership of the team and for ensuring that Health & Safety policies and procedures are effectively embedded across projects, sites and office environments in compliance with local and international rules and regulations. The role holder must take a 'hands on' approach to all aspects of the role.
Responsibilities
Business Leadership• Assist in the leadership and support of the team• Carry out Health and Safety inspections of project sites and company facilities as directed • Produce timely, accurate and detailed reports of inspections, including time and date stamped photographs• To advise the client and WSP management of any major non-compliances immediately• Carry out Health and Safety audits as required and produce an audit report• Review and comment on contractors Method Statements and Risk Assessments for compliance• Undertake tool box talks on site, as and when required to promote Health and Safety Awareness• Maintain a current knowledge of Local and International Health and Safety Rules and Regulations• Lead by example and always adhere to the best Health and Safety practices• Ensure your time is utilised efficiently and effectively at all times across your projects• Communicate effectively with site personnel and colleagues to promote Health and Safety at Work• Support the delivery of training and awareness sessions as required• Attend and contribute too team and project meetings as required• Ensure QMS and Project Lifecycle compliance across the team and projects• Ensure that Health & Safety is embedded into all work practices in line with company policies• Input into the recruitment and selection process• Contribute to the development and delivery of training and awareness sessions as required• Contribute to the development and implementation of the business unit (BU) strategy, including the companies approach to sustainability• Attend team meetings and lead project team meetings. Cascade relevant information and encourage feedback from team• Complete the companies e-learning courses • Provide regular project status and financial performance updates to line managerBusiness Development• Contribute to business development activities through participation in external market profile raising activities and functions• Actively develop external and internal client relationships• Proactively co sell other WSP ME services and where applicable the wider business• Provide technical leadership to respond to prequalification documents, Request for Price (RFPs) and other client inquiriesProject Leadership• To ensure statutory and regulatory requirements are met• Support the accurate and timely recognition of revenue for own projects and projects led by direct reportsTechnical• Conduct and oversee audits and reviews of the environment, practices and behaviours across site and offices• Lead the development of policies and review compliance as required• Provide advice and guidance on all aspects of Health & Safety on site and in the office environment• Analyse statistics of all accidents, near misses, dangerous occurrence, with the view of making recommendations Lead the investigation and close out of all safety actions for investigations or inspections • Issue safety notice for unsafe work and follow through for immediate rectification• Prepare and submit Health & Safety reports to the client as required• Provide support and guidance to Technical Working Group (TWG)• Keep up to date with industry developments with respect to own discipline and understand and appreciate the basic technical principles and drivers of other disciplines• Develop the capabilities of direct reports
Requirements
• Degree qualified with a minimum 5 years post graduate experience• Chartered Member of associated Professional body or Member giving eligibility to become Chartered• Regional Experience preferred• NEBOSH International Certificate• IOSH Working Safely• O (more...)
